article_title: U.S. Producer Prices Rose 0.1% in January
article_text:
WASHINGTON—A gauge of business prices rose in January, though overall inflation pressure remained muted.

The producer price index, which measures the prices companies receive for goods and services, advanced 0.1% in January from the prior month, the Labor Department said Wednesday. Excluding volatile food and energy categories, core prices...
